{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 263 |organ = SC |date = January 24 |year = 1969 |meeting = 1463 |code = S/RES/263 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/263(1969) |for = |abstention = |against = |subject = Working languages of the Security-Council |result = Adopted |image = |caption = }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 263''', adopted on January 24, 1969, after the [[United Nations General Assembly|General Assembly]] passed [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 2479|Resolution 2479]] extolling the virtues of expanded working languages, the Council decided to include [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]] among the working languages of the Security Council.
The resolution was adopted without vote.
